To create an inverted mask in the Flash Professional IDE Choose the properties panel of the image you want masked, select "Display" -> "Blending" -> "Layer" Then select your mask, and choose "Display -> "Blending" -> "Erase" You'll see something like this:package flash.display.DisplayObject{   public class ObjectA   {     ...     ObjectB.blendMode = BlendMode.LAYER;     addChild(ObjectB);     ...     ObjectC.blendMode = BlendMode.ERASE;     ObjectB.addChild(ObjectC);   }}private function createInvertedMask(mcToBeMasked:MovieClip):void {        mcToBeMasked.blendMode = BlendMode.LAYER;        var invertedMask:Sprite = new Sprite();        invertedMask.graphics.beginFill(0x0, 1);        invertedMask.graphics.drawRect(640, 395, 630, 395);        invertedMask.blendMode = BlendMode.ERASE;        mcToBeMasked.addChild(invertedMask);    }